    "recap_headline": "Marshall University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "Buy Tickets Here\n|\nBox Score (PDF)\n|\nChampionship Fund\nSTATESBORO, Ga. \u2013\nThe Marshall University Baseball team (13-8, 5-0 SBC) won its fifth straight Sun Belt Conference game and clinched its fourth straight series this season with a 13-5 victory on Saturday in Statesboro, Georgia, over Georgia Southern.\n\"Another win and another solid pitching performance backed up by really good defense,\" Herd Baseball Head Coach\nGreg Beals\nsaid. \"The real story today was our offense though, we had a great approach and gave tough at bats all day long.\"\nOliver Service\nwent a perfect 4-for-4 at the plate with two runs scored and a homer.\nTyler Kamerer\nhad a 3-for-4 day with four runs scored and a triple as\nCooper Hinson\nalso had a 3-for-4 day with a pair of RBI and a double.\nJackson Halter\ncollected three hits and three RBI with\nCleary Simpson\ndriving home a team-high four RBI.\nStarting pitcher\nDrew Harlow\nearned his third win of the season with 6.0 innings of work allowing three runs working around six hits and four walks with a strikeout.\nService led off the scoring with a one-out solo homer, his second of the season, in the top of the second.\nThe Eagles tallied a pair in the bottom half of the frame, but the Herd bats kicked into gear. In the top of the third, MU loaded the bases to start the frame with Evan Botton and Kamerer singling and Halter being hit by a pitch.\nThen an\nAJ Havrilla\nbases loaded walk, a balk, and sacrifice flies from Hinson and Simpson capped off a four-run frame to take a 5-2 advantage.\nThen in the fourth, a Halter RBI single made it 6-2. Another two runs crossed in the fifth on a Simpson ground and a\nWil Gubba\nsingle to right, extending the advantage to 8-2.\nGS struck for a run in the bottom of the fifth, but MU answered with Kamerer crossing home on a Hinson RBI single and Halter scoring on a Simpson sacrifice fly to take a 10-3 lead.\nThe Herd tallied its final three runs of the ballgame on a Halter two-RBI double and another Simpson groundout to go up 13-3.\nThe Eagles added a run in each of the seventh and ninth innings, but Marshall shutdown the game with\nHunter Richardson\nand\nA.J. McAninch\neach striking out a pair across the final three frames.\nUP NEXT\nThe Herd looks to complete a series sweep in Statesboro on Sunday at 1 p.m. against the Eagles.\nTo donate to the Championship Fund for Marshall baseball, please click\nHERE\n. All proceeds go directly to the Marshall baseball team.\nPar Mar is the presenting sponsor of the 2026 Marshall baseball team. Par Mar is the official convenience store of Marshall Athletics.\nFor all the latest information about Marshall baseball, follow @herdbaseball on Twitter and Instagram.\nTo follow all Thundering Herd sports and get live stats, schedules and free live audio, download the Marshall Athletics App for iOS and Android.\n---HerdZone.com---",
